Read data

d <- as.matrix(read.csv('imageSVD.csv', header=F))

Functions

Cumulative variance

cumVar <- function(A){
   eigs <- svd(A)$d ^2
   return(cumsum(eigs / sum(eigs)))
}

Compression

Bellow I use built in svd() function.

compress <- function(d, k){
    svd <- svd(d, nu=k, nv=k)
    sigma <- svd$d
    U <- svd$u
    V <- svd$v
    Ak <- matrix(rep(0, len=dim(d)[1]^2), nrow=dim(d)[1])
    for(i in 1:k){
        Ak <- Ak + sigma[i] * U[,i] %*% t(V[,i])
    }
    return(Ak)
}

Question(a)

minNumToPreserve <- which(cumVar(d)>=0.9)[1]

So, 18 singular values/vectors are needed to preserve 90% of variance of the original image.

Question (b)

plot(cumVar(d), xlab='k', ylab='Cummulative varience')

Question (c)

Ak <- compress(d, minNumToPreserve)

Pixels:

\(A_k (1,1)=\) 15.2724772.
\(A_k (256,256)=\) -10.2584093.
\(A_k (512,512)=\) -53.5648755.

Question (d)

err <- norm(d - Ak, type="2") 
varLost <- 1 - cumVar(d)[minNumToPreserve]

Error from built-in function is 1788.91309. This is \(L_2\)-norm.
Error from singular values can be calculated as variance lost, which is 9.5054943%.
